 chrs is the csu’s common human resources system, built in peoplesoft hcm 9.2. this system manages all aspects of an employee’s records at sjsu including position, job and personal data; temporary academic employment; student employment; benefits; time and absence data; and more. all csu campuses will exist in one database. sjsu is part of the second wave of campuses implementing the new system and will begin the project in june of 2021. the system is set to go live in december of 2022. to learn more, visit the chancellor’s office chrs website . chrs will be an upgraded version of peoplesoft (hr only) that is shared with all other csu campuses and the chancellor’s office. to learn more about the anticipated changes, please see chrs changes . university-personnel@sjsu.edu up north: 408-924-2450 up south: 408-924-2250  up webmaster up north administration building 242 up south upd building 3rd floor 